  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Defining Project Infrastructure**\n\nI\'m now focused on the foundational aspects: constructing `server.ts` to manage API endpoints and leverage Vite effectively for both development and production. Concurrently, the initial B2B SaaS landing page within `src/App.tsx` is under development.\n\n\n**Generating Standalone HTML**\n\nI\'ve shifted focus to creating a standalone HTML landing page. I\'m prioritizing its structure and design. Specifically, I\'m defining the color palette (deep navy, electric indigo, white, light gray, amber), and font stack. The first section will be a hero section with a sticky navigation bar with the logo on the left. I\'m aiming for a download option to deliver the complete HTML file directly.\n\n\n**Designing Landing Page Sections**\n\nI\'m now outlining the landing page content. I\'ve drafted a compelling hero section featuring a power headline about saving time, and a subheadline explaining our custom AI automations. I am now planning the CTA buttons and a trust bar with key stats. The plan is to include a light-weight animated SVG or CSS diagram. Following this, I\'ll build the pain agitation section. I plan to use a 6-card grid with custom icons and one-liners. I\'ve also planned a solution/how-it-works section that follows.\n\n\n**Adding Social Proof & Lead Capture**\n\nI\'m currently working on incorporating social proof and a lead capture form. Specifically, I\'m designing three testimonial cards, each with placeholders for quotes, names, titles, company information, and results. I\'m also including a logo strip featuring generic industry icons. For the lead capture form, I\'m creating a dark, full-width section with a compelling headline, subtext, and standard input fields. I\'m focusing on user experience, including an interactive success animation and trust signals.\n\n\n**Finalizing Standalone HTML**\n\nI\'m now integrating the FAQ section with accordion-style Q&As and a final CTA strip. I\'ve composed the straightforward, centered call to action. Next, I\'ll incorporate the footer with logo, tagline, links, and copyright information. I\'m also planning mobile exit-intent stickiness with a subtle bottom bar and integration notes. Finally, I\'m confirming that the `/public` directory exists and that I can include Tailwind CSS via CDN.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 84
      nanos: 748474234
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
