  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Discovering The Right Page**\n\nI\'ve confirmed that `/public/landing.html` perfectly fits the criteria. It\'s exactly what the user wanted: a complete, standalone, production-ready, highly polished, zero-dependency HTML landing page that captures business leads. I\'m now moving on to the next step.\n\n\n**Integrating The Landing Page**\n\nI\'m now thinking about how `/src/App.tsx` can serve as the framework for the highly polished, standalone landing page. The goal is to make it interactive with React features. I\'m especially excited about creating an ROI Calculator Widget. The widget will allow users to input data and receive instant calculations for hours recaptured, annual savings, and automation ROI timeframe. This includes pre-filling the lead form with their values!\n\n\n**Designing The Automation**\n\nI\'m now focused on the interactive backend with a B2B terminal or card display. When the user submits, it\'ll trigger a POST request to `/api/lead` with a loading spinner. The backend uses Express and makes a Gemini call with the provided information. It then crafts personalized automation recommendations, complete with scoring and metrics. If there\'s no API key, it falls back to sandbox data with a notification. My next step is to make a downloadable file for the user.\n\n\n**Adding Download Functionality**\n\nI\'m now integrating a \"Download Standalone HTML Landing\" feature. I envision a sleek toggle or button that, when activated, reveals a slide-over or modal with the raw HTML, a copy-to-clipboard button, and a download-to-disk button. This covers the export requirement perfectly. I\'ve also re-confirmed that every requirement has been met, including the single-view constraint, visual style using navy, indigo, white, slate, and amber, a responsive design approach that\'s desktop-first but with mobile first code, and zero mock data dependency.\n\n\n**Incorporating Lucide Icons**\n\nI\'m now integrating Lucide icons into the `/src/App.tsx` React component. I\'m especially happy that `lucide-react` is pre-installed. I\'ll import a set of icons for the visual feel. I\'ll need to confirm that Tailwind is active, then design a majestic `/src/App.tsx` component that is fully reactive. The next step will be designing the ROI calculator, which I plan to place below the Hero section with sliders to allow immediate calculations of savings.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will edit `/src/App.tsx` using `create_file` (with Overwrite set to true) to implement the high-converting conversion landing page of stoneVEIL Operations LLC in React. This frontend integrates a live, fully response-active Lead Capture engine, an interactive ROI Calculator, a standalone HTML code downloader/copy panel, and client-side animated state transitions."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 6
      nanos: 308230561
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
